### Expose RxStorage in Electron Main Process (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/electron.md

This code snippet demonstrates how to expose an RxStorage in the main process using the RxDB Electron plugin. It utilizes `exposeIpcMainRxStorage` to wrap a memory storage and make it available for IPC communication. Ensure `nodeIntegration` is enabled in your Electron BrowserWindow options.

```typescript
//  main.js
const { exposeIpcMainRxStorage } = require('rxdb/plugins/electron');
const { getRxStorageMemory } = require('rxdb/plugins/storage-memory');
app.on('ready', async function () {
    exposeIpcMainRxStorage({
        key: 'main-storage',
        storage: getRxStorageMemory(),
        ipcMain: electron.ipcMain
    });
});
```

