### RxDB Attachment Compression with 'attachments-compression' Plugin

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-attachment.md

Demonstrates how to use the 'attachments-compression' plugin in RxDB to compress attachments, saving disc space. This plugin uses the Compression Streams API, which has limited browser support. It requires importing specific functions and configuring the storage and schema.

```typescript
import {
    wrappedAttachmentsCompressionStorage
} from 'rxdb/plugins/attachments-compression';

import { getRxStorageIndexedDB } from 'rxdb-premium/plugins/storage-indexeddb';

// create a wrapped storage with attachment-compression.
const storageWithAttachmentsCompression = wrappedAttachmentsCompressionStorage({
    storage: getRxStorageIndexedDB()
});

const db = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'mydatabase',
    storage: storageWithAttachmentsCompression
});


// set the compression mode at the schema level
const mySchema = {
    version: 0,
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
        // .
        // .
        // .
    },
    attachments: {
        compression: 'deflate'  // <- Specify the compression mode here. OneOf ['deflate', 'gzip']
    }
};

/* ... create your collections as usual and store attachments in them. */
```

