This snippet shows how to consume the RxStorage exposed from the main process within an Electron renderer process using the RxDB Electron plugin. It uses `getRxStorageIpcRenderer` to create a remote storage instance, which is then used to initialize an RxDatabase. This allows renderer processes to interact with data stored in the main process.

