### Importing Storage Plugins in RxDB (Prefixed)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/releases/14.0.0.md

RxDB 14.0 standardizes storage plugin imports by prefixing them with 'storage-'. This change aims to improve naming conventions and organization. For example, to import the Dexie storage, you would now use 'rxdb/plugins/storage-dexie' instead of the older 'rxdb/plugins/dexie'.

```typescript
// Instead of 
// import { getRxStorageDexie } from 'rxdb/plugins/dexie';
// it is now
import { getRxStorageDexie } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-dexie';
```

