### Create RxDB Database and Collection (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/replication-webrtc.md

Sets up a new RxDB database using the localStorage storage and defines a 'todos' collection with a specific schema. It also demonstrates inserting an initial document into the collection. This is a prerequisite for replication.

```typescript
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb/plugins/core';
import { getRxStorageLocalstorage } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-localstorage';
const db = await createRxDatabase({
  name: 'myTodoDB',
  storage: getRxStorageLocalstorage()
});

await db.addCollections({
  todos: {
    schema: {
      title: 'todo schema',
      version: 0,
      type: 'object',
      primaryKey: 'id',
      properties: {
        id:      { type: 'string', maxLength: 100 },
        title:   { type: 'string' },
        done:    { type: 'boolean', default: false },
        created: { type: 'string', format: 'date-time' }
      },
      required: ['id', 'title', 'done']
    }
  }
});

// insert an example document
await db.todos.insert({
  id: 'todo-1',
  title: 'P2P demo task',
  done: false,
  created: new Date().toISOString()
});
```

